      </prefercite>
      <bioghist id="aspace_482703770b03df63784389730d7cf76d">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>William Walter Meyer (1887-1969): general counsel of the New York, New Haven, and Hartford Railroad. Karl Frederick Meyer (1891-1971): real estate agent; officer with the Detroit Trust Company. George Arthur Meyer (1894-1971): chairman, Modern Languages Department of Utah State University; author of several books. Charles Grafton Meyer (1896-): lawyer; vice President and director of Citizens Saving Bank, Stamford, Conn.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_c95c3605e640a89f2d16078a646a7a60">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Correspondence, photographs, clippings and memorabilia of the Meyer family of Ada, Ohio documenting family activities during World War I. The five brothers, all Yale graduates, served overseas.</p>
      </scopecontent>
